      "description": "Sliver is a publicly available cross-platform adversary emulation framework written in Go. It was used by attackers in the CL-CRI-1036 campaign to facilitate post-exploitation activities such as lateral movement and credential dumping. The attackers deployed a Linux version of Sliver as a TCP Pivot implant.",
